title: CORONA: Update on 91 bridge collapse expected Wednesday
text:
By PATRICK O’NEILL / STAFF WRITER
Published: Oct. 13, 2015 7:06 p.m. CORONA: Update on 91 bridge collapse expected Wednesday Print Photo Share Pin It More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT On Friday, Oct. 9, a section of the 91 freeway on-ramp under construction above East Grand Boulevard in Corona dropped unexpectedly by more than a foot, snapping wooden support beams which in turn struck employees. , PATRICK O’NEILL, STAFF Related article » An update is expected Wednesday morning on the mishap that prompted a partial bridge collapse during the 91 freeway expansion project, injuring nine workers – seven of whom remain hospitalized.
The information is expected to be released during the Riverside County Transportation Commission's morning meeting.
As of Tuesday, transportation commission Deputy Director John Standiford said that he did not have enough information to provide updates on the workers.
Spokespersons at Atkinson Walsh, project contractors, have not responded to repeated inquiries about the incident.
The incident occurred on Friday, Oct. 9, when a section of the 91 freeway onramp under construction above East Grand Boulevard in Corona dropped unexpectedly by more than a foot, snapping wooden support beams, which, in turn, struck employees.
Three victims were initially reported in critical condition.
Jarrell Boyd, a 33-year-old Riverside native, sustained major injuries, including a broken shoulder, neck and femur, fiancee Kendra Santos said Monday night. Doctors have drilled a hole in Boyd’s skull to monitor swelling. Santos was told Boyd may not survive.
